New Records: Chris Woakes has gone level with Ian Botham on 30 wickets, the joint-most for England at World Cups.
Key Match Events: Ben Stokes smacked 108 off 84 as England post 339-9 in Pune
England win by 160 runs to boost Champions Trophy qualification chances
Rashid & Moeen takes three wickets each, Willey strikes twice, Woakes claims one and Barresi run out
Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands captain Scott Edwards: 'We need to find that balance better'
Michael Vaughan: 'I'm not one for swapping and changing a coach that won a T20 World Cup a year ago.'
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes: 'I'm more pleased for us to get a victory over the line, it's been a tough World Cup and nice to get back to winning ways today.'
England captain Jos Buttler: 'We were desperate for the win.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England have climbed to seventh, and as things stand would qualify for the Champions Trophy in Pakistan in 2025.
